        <td style="height:37px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Gear Pressure Angle</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the angle between the &apos;Line of Action&apos; and the Line Perpendicular to the Line-of-centers.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Gear Pressure Angle</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is most easily appreciated when the gears are positioned so that the contact point coincides with the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Gears-Line-of-Centres" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">&apos;Line-of-centers&apos;</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, as in the images above. The &apos;Line-of-Action&apos; and the perpendicular to &apos;Line-of-centers&apos; are shown for </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Gear Pressure Angles of 20º, 25,º &amp; 14.5º.</text></para>
        </td>
